DictStillThrowsOnSort
/ Regression anchor: with the `where T : item` constraint locked and every value `: item`,
/ sorting a list of dicts is still rejected — `item` carries no ordering for dict to leak,
/ regardless of the kind of the dict's values. PLang surfaces it as an error (not a thrown
/ exception), so the on-error handler catches it.
- set %scores% = [{"score":10}, {"score":20}]
- sort %scores%, on error call Caught
- assert %caught% is true

Caught
- set %caught% = true
